definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  (24R,25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha,24-tetrahydroxy-5beta-cholestanoyl-CoA -eq- (24E)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholest-24-enoyl-CoA + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N(4)-acetyl-L-2,4-diaminobutyrate -eq- ectoine + H(2)O.

Catalysis of the reactions -  1,5-anhydro-D-fructose -eq- 2-hydroxy-2-(hydroxymethyl)-2H-pyran-3(6H)-one + H2O -  (1a) 1,5-anhydro-D-fructose -eq- 1,5-anhydro-4-deoxy-D-glycero-hex-3-en-2-ulose + H2O and (1b) 1,5-anhydro-4-deoxy-D-glycero-hex-3-en-2-ulose -eq- 2-hydroxy-2-(hydroxymethyl)-2H-pyran-3(6H)-one.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1,5-anhydro-D-fructose -eq- 1,5-anhydro-4-deoxy-D-glycero-hex-3-en-2-ulose + H2O.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucuronan -eq- an oligosaccharide with 4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl end + (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucuronan. This reaction is the eliminative cleavage of (1--gt-4)-beta-D-glucuronans to give oligosaccharides with 4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl groups at their non-reducing ends. Complete degradation of glucuronans results in the formation of tetrasaccharides.

Catalysis of the reaction -  an N-acetylneuraminate glycoside -eq- 2,7-anhydro-alpha-N-acetylneuraminate + an alpha-sialyl group. This reaction is the elimination of alpha-sialyl groups in N-acetylneuraminic acid glycosides, releasing 2,7-anhydro-alpha-N-acetylneuraminate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-fructopyranosyl-(2--gt-6)-[D-fructofuranosyl-(2--gt-6)]n-D-fructofuranoside -eq- beta-D-fructopyranosyl-(2--gt-6)-[D-fructofuranosyl-(2--gt-6)](n-1)-D-fructofuranoside + di-beta-D-fructofuranose 2,6' - 2',6-dianhydride. This reaction is the production of di-beta-D-fructofuranose 2,6' - 2',6-dianhydride (DFA IV) by successively eliminating the diminishing (2--gt-6)-beta-D-fructan (levan) chain from the terminal D-fructosyl-D-fructosyl disaccharide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  [(2--gt-1)-beta-D-fructosyl](n) -eq- [(2--gt-1)-beta-D-fructosyl](n-1) + alpha-D-fructofuranose-beta-D-fructofuranose 1,2' - 1,2'-dianhydride. This reaction is the production of alpha-D-fructofuranose beta-D-fructofuranose 1,2' - 2,1'-dianhydride (DFA I) by successively eliminating the diminishing (2--gt-1)-beta-D-fructan (inulin) chain from the terminal D-fructosyl-D-fructosyl disaccharide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  [(2--gt-1)-beta-D-fructosyl](n) -eq- [(2--gt-1)-beta-D-fructosyl](n-1) + alpha-D-fructofuranose beta-D-fructofuranose 1,2' - 2,3'-dianhydride. This reaction is the production of alpha-D-fructofuranose beta-D-fructofuranose 1,2' - 2,3'-dianhydride (DFA III) by successively eliminating the diminishing (2--gt-1)-beta-D-fructan (inulin) chain from the terminal D-fructosyl-D-fructosyl disaccharide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  dermatan sulfate -eq- n 4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl-(1,3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4-sulfate. This reaction is the eliminative cleavage of dermatan sulfate containing 1,4-beta-D-hexosaminyl and 1,3-beta-D-glucurosonyl or 1,3-alpha-L-iduronosyl linkages to disaccharides containing 4-deoxy-beta-D-gluc-4-enuronosyl groups to yield a 4,5-unsaturated dermatan-sulfate disaccharide (DeltaUA-GalNAC-4S). Chondroitin sulfate B is also known as dermatan sulfate.

Catalysis of the endolytic cleavage of beta-1,4-galactosaminic bonds between N-acetylgalactosamine and either D-glucuronic acid or L-iduronic acid to produce a mixture of Delta4-unsaturated oligosaccharides of different sizes that are ultimately degraded to Delta4-unsaturated tetra- and disaccharides.
Catalysis of the exolytic cleavage of disaccharide residues from the non-reducing ends of both polymeric chondroitin sulfates and their oligosaccharide fragments.

Catalysis of the reaction -  [eIF5A-precursor]-lysine + spermidine -eq- [eIF5A-precursor]-deoxyhypusine + propane-1,3-diamine. Four sub-reactions have been identified,in which the intermediates remain tightly associated with the enzyme -  spermidine + NAD+ -eq- dehydrospermidine + NADH -  dehydrospermidine + [enzyme]-lysine -eq- N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[enzyme]-lysine + propane-1,3-diamine -  N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[enzyme]-lysine + [eIF5A-precursor]-lysine -eq- N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[eIF5A-precursor]-lysine + [enzyme]-lysine -  N-(4-aminobutylidene)-[eIF5A-precursor]-lysine + NADH + H+ -eq- [eIF5A-precursor]-deoxyhypusine + NAD+.
Catalysis of the removal of 8-oxo-7,8-dihydroguanine bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the oxidized purine and the deoxyribose sugar.

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + sterol(in) -eq- ADP + phosphate + sterol(out).

A protein complex that forms a coat structure on vesicles involved in exocytosis of proteins from the trans-Golgi network to the cell surface -  in Saccharomyces, the complex contains Chs5p, Chs6p, and Chs6p paralogues.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a sequence of guanine residues in an RNA molecule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the estrogen response element (ERE), a conserved sequence found in the promoters of genes whose expression is regulated in response to estrogen.
Facilitates the displacement of one strand of an RNA-RNA duplex and its replacement with a different strand of higher complementarity.
The space enclosed by the double membrane of a cyanelle.

Catalysis of the reaction -  deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + DNA(n+1) -  the synthesis of DNA from deoxyribonucleotide triphosphates in the presence of a nucleic acid template and a 3'hydroxyl group.
